
## MASTER SPECIFICATION SHEET: ADVANCED HYDROTHERMAL CLIMATE CORE## [1] STRUCTURAL ENVELOPE DIMENSIONS

       EXTERIOR FACE (Weather Boundary)
+---------------------------------------------+

|  2x4 LSL Stud Layer (3.5" Depth, 16" o.c.)  |
+=============================================+

|                                             |
|  Continuous Divorced Core (6.0" Depth)      |
|  - Encapsulated in Closed-Cell Spray Foam   |
|                                             |
+=============================================+

|  2x4 LSL Stud Layer (3.5" Depth, 16" o.c.)  |
+---------------------------------------------+

|  Airtight Gasketed Drywall Face             |
+---------------------------------------------+
       INTERIOR FACE (Conditioned Space)


* Total Assembly Thickness: 13.0 Inches
* Framing Selection: 2x4 Laminated Strand Lumber (LSL) / Laminated Veneer Lumber (LVL)
* Framing Grid Geometry: 16 Inches On-Center (22% Total Framing Fraction)
* Divorced Cavity Isolation: 6.0-Inch completely independent clear air gap separating interior and exterior framing planes
* Top Boundary Connector: Factory-engineered parallel-chord roof trusses / energy heel trusses spanning both top plates across the 13-inch footprint. Eliminates the need for manual wood gussets.
* Air Seal Intersection: Airtight drywall method combined with compressed EPDM/closed-cell drywall gasket tape applied to the 1.5-inch face of the LSL studs before sheet placement. Prevents framing-edge micro-fissures from leaking air.

------------------------------
## [2] THERMODYNAMIC CORRIDOR & THERMAL BATTERY## Core Thermal Battery Matrix

* Primary Vessel: Vertical steel-jacketed water columns acting as a fluid thermal mass.
* Storage Limit Strategy: Active predictive feed-forward loops throttling input below a hard 185°F ceiling to prevent phase-change boiling.
* Input Array (Optics): Spherical Fresnel "Ray-Bender" lenses feeding solar energy down highly reflective mirrored tubes.
* Summer Rejection Mechanism: Mirrored assemblies mounted onto horizontal rotational bearings. Automatically pivots away to shade the column core when the indoor space demands cooling, allowing the cold water mass to act as a sensible cooling sink.
* Emergency Energy Injection: Multi-fuel biomass furnace (capable of running on wood pellets or corn) utilizing a secondary exterior-drawn air loop to prevent home depressurization. Combustible air outputs loop through a bypass duct network wrapping around the Trombe column jacket, slow-charging the core mass.

------------------------------
## [3] UNDER-FLOOR DOUBLE PLENUM PLUMBING## Air Circulation & Purification Map

* Crawl Space Design: Completely sealed, insulated, encapsulated double-plenum floor footprint.
* Filtration Barrier: Industrial-grade HEPA filtration system positioned immediately ahead of the primary air routing loops.
* Latent Load Regulator: Polymer desiccant mats separating the supply plenum from the return plenum. Handles moisture passively during night runs.
* Active Mechanical Dehumidifier: Split DX dehumidifier working in tandem with a low-BTU air conditioning split compressor to separate latent moisture management from sensible temperature cooling cycles.

------------------------------
## [4] POWER MANAGEMENT & ELECTRICAL MATRIX## Split-Voltage Hybrid System

* High-Voltage Generation: 18.75 kW Solar PV Array configured in high-voltage series strings (150V–250V DC) to minimize voltage drop between the roof and the central power plant.
* Power Core Capacity: 30 kWh Centralized LiFePO4 battery bank configured to a native 48V DC bus to balance efficiency and safe current loads.
* Heavy Lifting AC Bus (120V/240V AC via Inverter): Powers the split air conditioner compressor, high-pressure dehumidifier pump, and the multi-fuel furnace ignition/auger assemblies.
* Low Voltage DC Bus (Native 12V DC): Fed via industrial 48V-to-12V buck converters located at regional sub-panels. Runs the microcontrollers, communication networks, LED lighting, and motorized mechanical components.

## 12V DC Mechanical Air Control

* Damper Selection: Commercial-grade Belimo 12V DC/proportional high-torque actuators (45 to 90 in-lbs).
* Parasitic Load Prevention: Internal mechanical braking design with pulsed software signaling. Actuators draw near-zero wattage once their 90-second mechanical stroke completes.
* Wiring Specification: Multi-strand copper conductors (resistant to low-frequency equipment vibration).

------------------------------
## [5] MICROCONTROLLER DETECTIVE ARCHITECTURE## The 8-Zone Smart Telemetry Bus

   1. Zone 1: Open Air Living Space (Sensible and Latent Comfort Matrix)
   2. Zone 2: Crawl Space / Primary Pressurized Supply Plenum
   3. Zone 3: Outer Steel Wall Surface Temperature of Trombe Column
   4. Zone 4: Internal Core Fluid Temperature of Trombe Column
   5. Zone 5: Convection Core Internal Heat Rod Temperature
   6. Zone 6: Multi-Fuel Furnace Duct Flow Exhaust Temperature
   7. Zone 7: External Ambient Environment Temperature
   8. Zone 8: Continuous Dew-Point Calculations (Active Humidity Nodes across all points)

## System Management Logic

* Primary Controller: Redundant Arduino hardware nodes running bare-metal C++ over a local hardwired RS-485 Modbus loop.
* Secondary Telemetry/Logging: Low-power localized Home Assistant server pulling real-time stats without access to critical relay safety lines.
* Fail-Safe Loops: Enabled Hardware Watchdog Timers (WDT) with Two-Out-of-Three (2oo3) voting logic scripts across microcontrollers to catch and bypass failed sensor anomalies.
* Power Loss Default: Shading mirrors held in active solar focus via a normally open low-power relay grid. Complete power depletion instantly triggers a fail-safe capacitor or battery backup to drop the relay, automatically rotating the optics into a safe shade alignment.

------------------------------
## [6] BOUNDARY PRESSURE SEALS

          HIGH-HUMIDITY AREA                     |  DRY HARDWARE AREA
=================================================|=========================
Stranded Cable Pack --> [ Mates to Marine Plug ] |

                             |                   |
                             v                   |
               +---------------------------------+

               |  Threaded Metal M12 Connector   |
               |  - Compression Gasket to Wall   |
               |  - Solid Molded Pins            | <-- Breaks inter-strand
               +---------------------------------+     air & capillary paths


* Penetration Strategy: Passing wires through pressure boundaries via True Pin-and-Socket Bulkhead Connectors instead of traditional pressure cable glands.
* Capillary Migration Protection: Solid molded glass/polymer pin inserts stop moisture and vapor tracking inside multi-strand wire insulation jackets.
* Low-Voltage Data Links: Threaded industrial M12 circular connectors with gold-plated contacts to prevent pin oxidation and maintain data integrity.
* High-Amperage Links: Industrial Deutsch DT or Amphenol Eco|mate connectors rated for 13A–25A current loads.
* Mechanical Wall Gasketing: Bulkhead connectors utilize closed-cell neoprene gaskets or marine-grade polyurethane adhesive (3M 5200) clamped directly to the framing surface.

